benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/admin/cache - Invalidates the given Cache if specified, otherwise invalidates all caches

covered: Valid Deletion scenarios are demonstrated by TC01 (invalidate all caches) and TC02 (invalidate specific cache).

Input validation and error handling cover non-existent caches (TC03), empty cacheName (TC05), very large cacheName (TC10), invalid characters (TC11), case-sensitivity (TC12), and regression on invalid formats (TC15).
Authorization and server robustness are exercised via unauthorized access (TC06) and system error (TC07).
Boundary and data-set variations include no caches (TC08), extra query parameters (TC09), and performance/concurrency tests (TC13, TC14).
Handling of not-alive caches is covered by TC04.
gaps: Caching headers validation: no tests asserting ETag/Cache-Control on DELETE responses.
Rate limiting/throttling: no tests for burst requests or 429 responses.
Soft-delete semantics: tests do not explicitly verify soft-deletion behavior for caches.
recommendations: Add tests validating caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) on DELETE responses where applicable.
Add rate limiting tests to verify behavior under high load (e.g., 429).
Clarify or add tests around soft-delete semantics for cache invalidation and ensure consistent behavior across edge cases.
